<text id="02-output-contract" title="Laravel Enterprise Patterns Output Contract" version="1.1.0" est_tokens="900" depth="essential">
  <summary>JSON Schema for the Laravel-patterns manifest this methodology produces. Validator enforces required keys + per-field constraints.</summary>

  <section title="Schema">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
  "$id": "https://faion.net/schemas/laravel-patterns.json",
  "type": "object",
  "required": ["laravel_version", "php_version", "uses_form_requests", "prevent_lazy_loading_enabled", "queue_jobs", "api_resources"],
  "properties": {
    "laravel_version": {"type": "string", "pattern": "^(10|11)\\."},
    "php_version": {"type": "string", "pattern": "^8\\.(2|3|4)"},
    "uses_form_requests": {"type": "boolean", "const": true},
    "prevent_lazy_loading_enabled": {"type": "boolean", "const": true},
    "queue_jobs": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["class", "implements_should_be_unique"],
        "properties": {
          "class": {"type": "string"},
          "implements_should_be_unique": {"type": "boolean", "const": true}
        }
      }
    },
    "api_resources": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["class", "uses_explicit_fields"],
        "properties": {
          "class": {"type": "string", "pattern": "Resource$"},
          "uses_explicit_fields": {"type": "boolean", "const": true}
        }
      }
    },
    "forbidden_patterns_found": {"type": "array", "items": {"type": "string"}, "maxItems": 0}
  }
}
]]></code>
  </section>

  <example valid="true">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "laravel_version": "11.0",
  "php_version": "8.3",
  "uses_form_requests": true,
  "prevent_lazy_loading_enabled": true,
  "queue_jobs": [{"class": "App\\Jobs\\ChargeInvoice", "implements_should_be_unique": true}],
  "api_resources": [{"class": "App\\Http\\Resources\\InvoiceResource", "uses_explicit_fields": true}],
  "forbidden_patterns_found": []
}
]]></code>
  </example>

  <example valid="false">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "laravel_version": "8.0",
  "php_version": "7.4",
  "uses_form_requests": false,
  "prevent_lazy_loading_enabled": false,
  "queue_jobs": [{"class": "ChargeInvoice", "implements_should_be_unique": false}],
  "api_resources": [{"class": "InvoiceResource", "uses_explicit_fields": false}],
  "forbidden_patterns_found": ["$request->all() in InvoiceController::store"]
}
]]></code>
    <note>Laravel + PHP versions too old; FormRequest off; lazy loading enabled; job not idempotent; Resource leaking fields.</note>
  </example>

  <section title="Forbidden patterns">
    <list>
      <item>`$request-&gt;all()` or `Model::create($request-&gt;all())`.</item>
      <item>`Mail::to(...)-&gt;send(...)` inside a `DB::transaction` block.</item>
      <item>`app(Service::class)` / `resolve(Service::class)` outside container bindings and tests.</item>
      <item>API Resource using `$this-&gt;toArray()` or spreading attributes.</item>
      <item>Queue job that mutates external state without `ShouldBeUnique`.</item>
    </list>
  </section>

  <reference path="scripts/validate-laravel-patterns.py">Validator script</reference>
</text>
